-- Mitsubishi Corp. Acquires 50% Stake in France Solar-Power Plant
-- B y   C h i s a k i   W a t a n a b e
-- 2013-01-07T03:31:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-07/mitsubishi-corp-acquires-50-stake-in-france-solar-power-plant.html
Mitsubishi Corp. (8058) ,  Japan ’s biggest
trading house by market value, acquired a 50 percent stake in a
solar power plant in  France  from EDF Energies Nouvelles SA,
Mitsubishi said in a statement.  Toul-Rosieres solar power plant tranche 1, which started
operations in June, has a capacity of 55 megawatts, according to
the statement.  Total project cost is about 22 billion yen ($250 million),
Mitsubishi said. The company didn’t say how much it paid for the
stake.  The move is the first time for Mitsubishi to acquire a
photovoltaic power generating asset in France, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
